SUPLINF.P:
b. What additional relocation, acquisition, and replacement housing waivers and alternative requirements should HUD consider that would assist and expedite community efforts to reduce future risk while minimizing displacement and ensuring fair treatment and protections to those whose property is acquired or who must move due to a CDBG-DR funded activity? For example, recent CDBG-DR notices waive (and provide alternative requirements to) several provisions of the Uniform Relocation Assistance and Real Property Acquisition Policies Act of 1970, as amended (42 U.S.C. 4601 
et seq.
) (URA), section 104(d) of the HCDA, and related CDBG programmatic requirements.
